11. Combination Mathematics
nCr = n!/r!*(n-r)!
 Example 6C2 = 6!/2!*4!

             6*5*4*3*2*1
 ==>      -----------------
           (2*1) *(4*3*2*1)

We can simply write
            6*5
 ==>      -------
           (2*1)
We can do 
           6      5 
 ==>      --- * ----
           1      2

so we can run the loop till r, for optimizing

#Combination formula will be used to find value of pascal traingle if row and column value is given.

Solution:-

  public static long nCr(int n, int r){
    long res=1;
    for(int i=0;i<r;i++){
      res= res*(n-i);
      res=res/(i+1);
    }
     return res;
  }
